				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Eye for an Eye" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>An innovative, dice driven game of arena combat. As an Occulite Chief it's up to&amp;nbsp;YOU&amp;nbsp;to defend your tribe's honour.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Eye for an Eye is an gladiator-like skirmish game played in an arena with spaces marked by hexes. Players control one character (usually an Occulite Tribal Chief) trying to settle a dispute with another tribe or tribes (the other players).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Unlike other skirmish games, Eye for an Eye can be played in both real time with a soundtrack timing the action, or in a turn based format. So you play the game at your own pace! &amp;#10;In the Realtime mode, there are no turns and players can call out and resolve actions whenever they want to trigger them.&amp;nbsp;&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#139;Actions are powered by allocating dice to different spaces on the player&amp;rsquo;s board and cards. Each character has its own set of skills and restrictions on dice placement. It is likely that you will quickly form a bond with your favourite.&amp;nbsp;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the turn based mode, players break up the action into short stints, allocating dice in realtime and then grabbing a turn order marker. Players then resolve 2 actions each in an order based on who grabbed which turn order marker.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play a single round in five minutes and an entire tournament in one hour in realtime OR play a turn based game in 20 to 30 minutes. The choice is yours!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;With several different game modes including:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Every Eye for Themselves&amp;#10;     Alliances&amp;#10;     Nymphlet Ceremony&amp;#10;     King of the Hill&amp;#10;     Domination&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;and 6 totally unique characters (with more on the way), Eye for an Eye has a huge amount of replayability.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
